{
  "target": "PriorPredictiveCheck",
  "kind": "analysis",
  "source": "RMC-BestFit/src/RMC.BestFit/Diagnostics/PriorPredictiveCheck.cs @ c2e6192 -- X12 exact oracle, emitter-verified against the real RMC.BestFit PriorPredictiveCheck and reproduced bit-identically by the C++/R/Python runners. PriorPredictiveCheck samples 200 parameter sets from the Normal model priors (seeded MersenneTwister -- NO MCMC chain), simulates a sample_size=30 dataset per draw, and summarizes the predictive mean/SD/min/max quantiles. Every draw is valid (number_of_valid_draws == 200); the summary quantiles reproduce to rel 1e-9 across C#/C++/R/Python (the prior-sampling MT is bit-exact).",
  "datasets": {
    "flow": [
      12500,
      15300,
      8900,
      22100,
      18700,
      14200,
      9800,
      28500,
      17400,
      11600
    ]
  },
